@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms & Conditions";
    ViewData["MetaDescription"] = "Read the Eventify Pro Terms and Conditions to learn about our platform usage rules, booking agreements, refund policies, and organizer responsibilities.";
    ViewData["MetaKeywords"] = "Terms and Conditions, user agreement, billing policy, refund terms, ticket scanning, organizer terms, Eventify Pro legal";
}

<section class="page-header footer-page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <span class="section-tag-enhanced"><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> Legal Desk</span>
        <h1>Terms & Conditions</h1>
        <p>Please read these platform usage rules, billing agreements, and gate scanning policies before using Eventify Pro.</p>
        
        <div class="page-header-meta">
            <span class="meta-item"><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Reading time: 7 mins</span>
            <span class="meta-item"><i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i> Last updated: June 1, 2026</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="content-page section enhanced-bg-glow">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="legal-layout-enhanced">
            
            <!-- Sticky Sidebar Table of Contents -->
            <aside class="legal-sidebar-enhanced">
                <div class="toc-header">
                    <i class="fas fa-list-ol"></i>
                    <span>Table of Contents</span>
                </div>
                <nav class="toc-list">
                    <a href="#acceptance" class="toc-link active" data-toc>1. Acceptance of Terms</a>
                    <a href="#accounts" class="toc-link" data-toc>2. User Roles & Accounts</a>
                    <a href="#organizers" class="toc-link" data-toc>3. Organizer Obligations</a>
                    <a href="#ticketing" class="toc-link" data-toc>4. Bookings & Paymob Fees</a>
                    <a href="#scanning" class="toc-link" data-toc>5. Gate Scanning Rules</a>
                    <a href="#liability" class="toc-link" data-toc>6. Limitation of Liability</a>
                </nav>
            </aside>

            <!-- Comprehensive Legal Content Panel -->
            <div class="legal-panel-enhanced">
                
                <!-- Section 1: Acceptance -->
                <section id="acceptance" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
                    <p>By registering an account, purchasing a ticket, creating an event, or downloading the QR scanning interface on <strong>Eventify Pro</strong>, you agree to be legally bound by these Terms & Conditions. These terms govern the relationship between Eventify Pro, event organizers, attendees, and gate scanner users. If you do not agree to all clauses outlined in this agreement, you must immediately cease using the platform and delete your account.</p>
                    <div class="legal-callout-info">
                        <h4><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Important Notice</h4>
                        <p>Eventify Pro acts solely as a technological intermediary connecting organizers and attendees. We are not responsible for event cancellations, venue security, or organizer financial default. All ticket payouts and credit card billing are securely managed by Paymob.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 2: User Roles & Accounts -->
                <section id="accounts" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>2. User Registration, Security & Roles</h2>
                    <p>To enjoy the features of Eventify Pro, users must create a verified account and choose a specific user role. You are solely responsible for preserving the confidentiality of your account credentials (password and emails). You agree to immediately notify us if you suspect any unauthorized breach or hijack of your dashboard.</p>
                    <p><strong>System Role Definitions:</strong></p>
                    <ul class="legal-list">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i> <strong>Admin:</strong> Exercises complete control over the system, monitors user role permissions, reviews feedback, and accesses system logs.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-user-tie"></i> <strong>Organizer:</strong> Creates event listings, establishes VIP/Regular ticket prices, defines ticket quantities, monitors financial stats, and receives Paymob payouts.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-user"></i> <strong>Attendee:</strong> Browses public events, purchases tickets, receives secure QR tickets via email, and reviews their active tickets.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-qrcode"></i> <strong>Scanner:</strong> Assigned by organizers to scan and validate attendee QR codes at event entry gates on event day.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 3: Organizer Obligations -->
                <section id="organizers" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>3. Organizer Code of Conduct & Fraud Prevention</h2>
                    <p>Organizers who publish listings on Eventify Pro must adhere to strict ethical and legal guidelines to ensure attendee trust and platform safety:</p>
                    <ul class="legal-list">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Authentic Event Postings:</strong> You must create genuine events, offering detailed, accurate descriptions of the dates, location, banner image, and ticket features.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Fraud Prevention:</strong> The creation of fake, misleading, or plagiarized events intended to misappropriate funds is strictly prohibited. Engaging in fraudulent event creation will result in immediate permanent account termination, freezing of Paymob payouts, and a direct referral to local law enforcement.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Honoring Capacity Limits:</strong> Organizers must establish realistic event capacity ceilings. Setting arbitrary ticket limits that exceed venue physical safety laws is prohibited.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 4: Bookings & Paymob Fees -->
                <section id="ticketing" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>4. Ticket Bookings, Payments, & Paymob Fees</h2>
                    <p>When an attendee books a ticket, they are entering a direct, legally binding contract with the event organizer. Eventify Pro operates the checkout portal through our integrated billing partner, <strong>Paymob</strong>.</p>
                    <p><strong>Transaction Fees:</strong> Eventify Pro charges a standardized platform processing fee for every ticket sold through our gateway. This fee is automatically deducted from the ticket price at checkout before payouts are routed to organizers.</p>
                    <p><strong>Refund Policy:</strong> Attendees agree that all refunds, cancellations, and exchanges are governed solely by the specific event organizer's policy. Eventify Pro is not liable to refund ticket costs or processing fees directly to attendees in the event of organizer default or event cancellation. If an organizer triggers a cancellation, funds will be refunded back to the attendee's original card through Paymob.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 5: Gate Scanning Rules -->
                <section id="scanning" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>5. Entrance Verification & QR Gate Scanning Rules</h2>
                    <p>To preserve event entry integrity, organizers designate scanner accounts to check guests in on event day. All scanner staff must adhere to the following rules:</p>
                    <p><strong>Good Faith Validation:</strong> Scanners must inspect tickets in good faith. Bypassing duplicate scan warnings, accepting payment bribes to let unauthorized guests inside, or scanning valid tickets multiple times to disrupt check-in databases is strictly prohibited and will lead to an immediate ban of the scanner account.</p>
                    <p><strong>Database Integrity:</strong> Scanners must only validate tickets using the official Eventify Pro camera scanning tool. Collecting, copying, or photographing attendee QR codes for separate, external use violates attendee privacy rights and is punishable by law.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 6: Limitation of Liability -->
                <section id="liability" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>6. Limitation of Liability & Internet Connectivity</h2>
                    <p>Eventify Pro provides the event management and QR generation software "as is" and "as available". We do not warrant that platform operations will be entirely uninterrupted, error-free, or secure at all times.</p>
                    <p><strong>Venue Cell Signals:</strong> Organizers and scanner staff understand that entrance QR verification requires a stable internet or cellular connection to validate codes against our database. Eventify Pro is not responsible for ticketing delays at gates caused by local telecom failures, weak venue cellular signals, or power outages. Organizers must prepare physical backup guest lists for emergency entry validation if internet connectivity is compromised.</p>
                </section>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@section Scripts {
    <script>
        // Smooth Table of Contents Active State Highlighting
        const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.legal-section');
        const tocLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.toc-link');

        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            let current = '';
            sections.forEach(section => {
                const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                const sectionHeight = section.clientHeight;
                if (pageYOffset >= (sectionTop - 150)) {
                    current = section.getAttribute('id');
                }
            });

            tocLinks.forEach(link => {
                link.classList.remove('active');
                if (link.getAttribute('href') === `#${current}`) {
                    link.classList.add('active');
                }
            });
        });
    </script>
}
